TERRAFORM:

- Terraform is IAC (Infrastructure as Code)
- It is open source tool
- Providers Hashicorp but IBM is aquired Hashicorp
- Terraform is designed by Go language
- we can write our code in two language
    - JSON
    - HCL (Hashicorp Language)
- All files should be .tf 


-------------------------------------------------

List files in order:

- Provider.tf   -> Need to add provider details
- main.tf       -> all resource details ex EC2, S3, VPC etc
- variables.tf  -> pass the values instead hard coding in main.tf
- output.tf     ->  to get output values like instance id, public ip etc
- terraform.tfvars


- access key and secret keys are stored in .aws folder in local machine
- Terraform Registry:
    - aws
    - Azure
    - GCP

--> Important commands in Terraform
    - Terraform init : initialize all working plugins to folder from terraform registry.
    - Terraform apply : Created resources as per main.tf
    - Terrform plan : 


-- Terraform init triggers to provider.tf -> terraform registry -> provider plugins -> working directory.
